<sec id="id-754dc748-1f6a-4f32-b1ed-fa91fd725e0b"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="8e309db9-cbb3-44da-fd09-f45e563f01c6" timestamp="1666959954691"?>Education in equality: from awareness-raising to training<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="8e309db9-cbb3-44da-fd09-f45e563f01c6"?></bold></title><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="de25a981-8ed0-4a83-a296-a2961b0967d7" text="Box 13 – Education in equality: from awareness-raising to training" timestamp="1666959945189"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="bca575f0-2a9a-4547-800d-c4703627a982" text="[To be drafted again on13, 16 and 17 ]comment suggesting to merge box a more operational mode + [Former box 13]" timestamp="1675426845854"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="9560f442-d81c-469d-b730-a2c382d58cc7" text="+ GB commentsee FR " timestamp="1670265760085"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="4646ade7-be9e-4f11-a952-3fe61ad96ebc" timestamp="1667311170946"?><p>Education plays an essential role in teaching gender equality between girls and boys. An educational approach must be developed to raise awareness and inform children of the importance of gender equality from the earliest age possible. Schools are places that develop <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4646ade7-be9e-4f11-a952-3fe61ad96ebc"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="4c72e4bf-18bd-4f9c-9c95-c52aa2022dd0" text="our " timestamp="1670265661101"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="d0fda480-b379-4530-dfea-2cc16428570e" timestamp="1667311170946"?>knowledge of life, of which <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d0fda480-b379-4530-dfea-2cc16428570e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="299294cf-3d4a-4615-fa05-aa5a56b622ad" timestamp="1670265667944"?>gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="299294cf-3d4a-4615-fa05-aa5a56b622ad"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="f442c380-d3d7-45a1-afa2-2da94e2bd246" timestamp="1667311170946"?>equality is a part. All th<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f442c380-d3d7-45a1-afa2-2da94e2bd246"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="2ec8a7bd-101d-4b4d-e48e-c64d72169546" text="e protagonists " timestamp="1674570526907"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="80140086-4c24-449a-8f78-1f6190668d4f" timestamp="1674570530343"?>ose working <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="80140086-4c24-449a-8f78-1f6190668d4f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="40b73bc5-d815-4d04-b42a-07a80117e780" timestamp="1667311170946"?>in education should be trained in gender equality to ensure success. Curricular and extra-curricular activities should also enable girls and boys to integrate knowledge and learning that are <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="40b73bc5-d815-4d04-b42a-07a80117e780"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="2048ae88-b599-4f46-9150-400dc82a0dc6" text="\"traditionally\"" timestamp="1670265593980"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="a07ecbc7-f9e9-4511-c009-20dd1465c8fd" timestamp="1670265600478"?>socially and culturally<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a07ecbc7-f9e9-4511-c009-20dd1465c8fd"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="b80d831e-c310-4f9d-ac48-08168dae56b1" timestamp="1667311170946"?> assigned to one sex or the other - for example, mixed sports activities in the early years, equal value given to sports practised by girls and boys (for example, football, ballet), manual work, workshop work, domestic work, among other activities. Parents should also actively participate alongside teachers.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b80d831e-c310-4f9d-ac48-08168dae56b1"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="2e47723f-db50-4a0f-dee3-da2a3799da3f" timestamp="1666959940241"?>Education in equality can offer a means of empowering girls and women and of teaching respect, and a means of prevention in the fight against sexual and gender-based violence. Learning how to respect gender equality should lead to the notion of <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2e47723f-db50-4a0f-dee3-da2a3799da3f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="3303831e-5db8-484d-ef0f-791e2b67d073" timestamp="1668691341221"?>gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3303831e-5db8-484d-ef0f-791e2b67d073"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="a1fc7bc3-3062-45f3-8633-7cf094d07008" timestamp="1666959940241"?>parity and of sharing between <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a1fc7bc3-3062-45f3-8633-7cf094d07008"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="dc3669b4-d334-4bcf-f05c-5b709c8ea702" timestamp="1669040218964"?>wo<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="dc3669b4-d334-4bcf-f05c-5b709c8ea702"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="71610a1a-2427-4722-ba11-9e0166490226" timestamp="1666959940241"?>men and <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="71610a1a-2427-4722-ba11-9e0166490226"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="08b308d5-e769-4040-c9e2-1aa99cf30bcc" text="wo" timestamp="1669040220916"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="7d462b69-fce8-4031-a1d1-f3cfa4fec090" timestamp="1666959940241"?>men.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7d462b69-fce8-4031-a1d1-f3cfa4fec090"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="07cc842c-fdce-43a3-cb73-a95658216ded" timestamp="1666959940241"?>Raising awareness of and spreading information about <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="07cc842c-fdce-43a3-cb73-a95658216ded"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="df6a2355-c96c-4e32-c784-766515e90edc" timestamp="1670265613278"?>gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="df6a2355-c96c-4e32-c784-766515e90edc"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="09d11c52-4161-491a-9ee2-5f63ad0479bc" timestamp="1666959940241"?>equality are the key words for a more egalitarian development between <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="09d11c52-4161-491a-9ee2-5f63ad0479bc"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="e8b5d382-733b-4aca-8150-c06272de1c9b" timestamp="1669040224396"?>wo<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e8b5d382-733b-4aca-8150-c06272de1c9b"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="5bb55a15-41ce-4968-d4cc-396d9c161596" timestamp="1666959940241"?>men and <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5bb55a15-41ce-4968-d4cc-396d9c161596"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="78c874fe-3b2c-4437-acd2-a3f1d3dfaa52" text="wo" timestamp="1669040226675"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="ff81290a-3296-4488-b4a0-bda28c87974d" timestamp="1666959940241"?>men<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ff81290a-3296-4488-b4a0-bda28c87974d"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="6338e0db-474d-495d-e54c-fece5cfa672f" timestamp="1670265626058"?>, girls and boys,<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6338e0db-474d-495d-e54c-fece5cfa672f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="241ec9f1-553c-4771-ffb5-ae73f6439c02" timestamp="1666959940241"?> for the current and future generations.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="241ec9f1-553c-4771-ffb5-ae73f6439c02"?></p><p/></sec>